<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lesser1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lesser,</orth> adj. == less; 1) opposed to larger: <cit><quote>the l. thing should not the greater hide,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 663" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 663</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the l. legs,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 108</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>l. linen,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.3.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 3, 24</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.10.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 10, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.3.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 3, 41</bibl>.<lb />2) opposed to greater: <cit><quote>l. noise,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1329" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1329</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>'tis the l. sin,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 114.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 114, 13</bibl></cit>; <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. V, 4, 108</bibl>. <cit><quote>with l. weight,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 109</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>grace,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 89</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>knowledge,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.1.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 1, 38</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>fear,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.42" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 2, 42</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>waste,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.103" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 103</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>l. than my name,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.137" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 137</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>cause,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 4.4.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 4, 10</bibl></cit> (reading of Q<hi rend="sub">2</hi>). <cit><quote>the greater scorns the l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 6</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>l. than Macbeth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.3.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 3, 65</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>malady,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 9</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>enmities,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.1.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 1, 43</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>villain,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.219" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 219</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) opposed to more: <cit><quote>more rage and l. pity,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 468" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 468</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>l. had been the thwartings of your dispositions,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 2, 20</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>